      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but it feels like the \"accuracy\" argument is used more than the other. like, is there actually any evidence that the old way was just wrong, or is the new stuff seen as the only way to teach it \"correctly\" now? feels like a lot of people are just being called names for disagreeing with the new stuff",
